`,e.jsx(n.h2,{id:"executive-summary",children:"Executive Summary"}),`
`,e.jsx(n.p,{children:"Tokens Studio for Figma is a powerful plugin that bridges the gap between design and development by enabling platform-agnostic design tokens within Figma. For Kosmos, Tokens Studio provides significant value by creating a single source of truth for design decisions, enabling efficient multi-brand/theme management, and streamlining the design-to-code workflow. Its ability to export tokens directly to developer-friendly formats addresses a key limitation of Figma Enterprise, making it particularly valuable for Kosmos team members working across both design and development. The free version offers sufficient functionality for teams getting started, with the Pro version becoming valuable as Kosmos grows more complex or requires advanced features like multi-file Git integration."}),`
`,e.jsx(n.h2,{id:"problem-statement",children:"Problem Statement"}),`
`,e.jsx(n.h3,{id:"the-design-development-gap-in-kosmos",children:"The Design-Development Gap in Kosmos"}),`
`,e.jsx(n.p,{children:"Figma Enterprise offers excellent capabilities for in-app design system management, collaboration, and variable controls. However, it has a significant limitation: the lack of robust, direct export features for developer handoff. This creates a disconnect between the design decisions made in Figma and their implementation in code for Kosmos."}),`
`,e.jsx(n.p,{children:"Key issues include:"}),`
`,e.jsxs(n.ul,{children:[`
`,e.jsxs(n.li,{children:[e.jsx(n.strong,{children:"Limited token export options"}),": Figma Enterprise lacks built-in tools to export tokens as CSS, SCSS, or Flutter code that Kosmos developers need."]}),`
`,e.jsxs(n.li,{children:[e.jsx(n.strong,{children:"Manual translation required"}),": Without proper tooling, Kosmos designers or developers must manually translate design tokens into code, introducing potential inconsistencies and errors."]}),`
`,e.jsxs(n.li,{children:[e.jsx(n.strong,{children:"Disconnected workflows"}),": Changes in design often require manual implementation in code, slowing down iteration cycles for Kosmos updates."]}),`
`,e.jsxs(n.li,{children:[e.jsx(n.strong,{children:"Scaling challenges"}),": As Kosmos grows, maintaining consistency across design and code becomes increasingly difficult without systematic solutions."]}),`
`]}),`
`,e.jsx(n.p,{children:"Tokens Studio specifically addresses these pain points by providing a bridge between Figma's design capabilities and the code implementation needs of the Kosmos development team."}),`
`,e.jsx(n.h2,{id:"key-features-analysis",children:"Key Features Analysis"}),`
`,e.jsx(n.h3,{id:"design-to-code-token-export-capabilities",children:"Design-to-Code Token Export Capabilities"}),`
`,e.jsx(n.p,{children:"Tokens Studio excels at translating design decisions into developer-friendly formats:"}),`
`,e.jsxs(n.ul,{children:[`
`,e.jsxs(n.li,{children:[e.jsx(n.strong,{children:"Cross-platform export"}),": Tokens Studio can export tokens as JSON for use in CSS, SCSS, Flutter, and other platforms via tools like Style Dictionary and figma2flutter."]}),`
`,e.jsxs(n.li,{children:[e.jsx(n.strong,{children:"Standardized output"}),": Provides consistent, structured output that can be directly integrated into development workflows."]}),`
`,e.jsxs(n.li,{children:[e.jsx(n.strong,{children:"Bidirectional sync"}),": Changes made in code repositories can be synced back to Figma, creating a true two-way workflow."]}),`
`,e.jsxs(n.li,{children:[e.jsx(n.strong,{children:"Reduced manual work"}),": Eliminates time-consuming and error-prone manual translation of design tokens into code."]}),`
`]}),`
`,e.jsx(n.p,{children:"For a small team of two managing a design system, these export capabilities are invaluable, as they reduce the workload of maintaining parallel systems and ensure design decisions are accurately reflected in code."}),`
